When Winfred Nzisa went into labour before 9 months and delivered her daughter weighing 700 grams, she thought she would be a statistic with a tragic ending. Newborn deaths in Kenya remain a key issue of public health concern, where 22 out of every one thousand newborns die every year. Dr. Mercy Korir reports in this episode of health digest, with kangaroo mother care, it is possible for mothers like Winfred, to go home with their newborns 